All 8 tests pass and the `experiment-done.txt` marker has been written. The Game of Life implementation is complete with full TDD cycle coverage:

1. Empty array → empty array
2. Single cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation)
4. Block (2x2) survives as still life
5. Vertical blinker → horizontal blinker
6. Cell with >3 neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
8. Negative coordinates handled correctly
